Syntax: poison:quinine

Applies quinine poison to your currently wielded weapon. Quinine has unique
effects distinct from the other two weapon poisons (arsenic and nightshade).
It is one of three weapon poisons available to rogue-line characters
(Cipher, Assassin, Warlock, Nightblade).

Each poison interacts differently with rogue openers such as Backstab and
Circle, producing additional effects on hit.

Restrictions:
  - Requires a weapon to be wielded.
  - Must have the skill learned.

See also: shelp poison:quinine poison:arsenic poison:nightshade poison weapon backstab
